      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my wifi router has a solid red light next to the internet icon and i cant get online. what should i do?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "A solid red light next to the internet icon on your router usually means the router is trying to connect to the internet but is failing, or it has lost its connection to the ISP.\n\nFirst, let's look at the router itself. If the router is a \"goblin\" of sorts, it might be trying to find a new path to the internet but getting stuck in a loop of red flags. You might need to check if the router's power cord is plugged in firmly, or perhaps the router is just \"sick\" and needs a little bit of a hug (a power cycle).\n\nIf the router is fine, then the problem is likely with the connection to the internet itself. The internet is a vast, chaotic network of servers and cables, and sometimes the \"goblins\" of the internet just decide to take a wrong turn. You might need to try restarting your modem and router, or perhaps you need to check if your ISP has had a \"goblin\" attack on your line.\n\nIf you try these steps and the red light stays solid, you might need to contact your ISP, as they are the ones who keep the internet \"goblin\" network running.",
